data.name: lbl_Main.Text
data.value: Usage of the program is effortless, all the tweaks categorized and listed below fetched from GitHub page of the Tzoptimizer. You can see description for each tweak by hovering mouse onto it. Once you selected tweaks that you want to apply just click 'Optimize' button to configure. Also, you can always take a look source code of Tzoptimizer and contribute to either tweaks or program itself in GitHub.

data.name: lbl_Reminder1.Text
data.value: Tzoptimizer only capable of doing registry editing stuff which isn't capable of increasing the performance by a huge portion. If you are seeking for real performance improvement, you can upgrade your hardware in the first place if you cannot:

data.name: lbl_Reminder2.Text
data.value: 1) If there is an obstructure that limits your hardware figure out what's and why? That may be power limit, temperature limit, and so on. You can monitor your temperatures and usages while gaming using MSI Afterburner OSD (On screen display).

data.name: lbl_Reminder3.Text
data.value: 2) Try to overclock if you are using desktop and you have good cooling solutions and good temperatures or try to undervolt if you have higher temperatures which is way more basic to do and not harmful at all except some unexpected reboots. You can use ThrottleStop to undervolt your CPU and MSI Afterburner to undervolt your GPU.

data.name: lbl_Reminder4.Text
data.value: 3) If you lack of memory then download and use Intelligent Standby List Cleaner, or you have suspicious about your computer has been slowed down recently try to reinstall your GPU driver first uninstalling it using Display Driver Uninstaller.

data.name: lbl_Reminder5.Text
data.value: 4) Disable Control Flow Guard (CFG) and High Precision Event Timer (HPET) and see if this works.

data.name: lbl_Revert.Text
data.value: You can easily revert tweak or tweaks you have done before just selecting them and clicking on 'Revert' button.
